sentences: Jameson Clark (born 1972 in Starr, South Carolina) is an American country music singer.
Between 2001 and 2002, he recorded for Capitol Records and charted two singles: "Don't Play Any Love Songs" and "You da Man", in addition to releasing an album titled Workin' on a Groove.
